1
00:00:03,760 --> 00:00:06,200
What?
-What... what did you do?

2
00:00:07,040 --> 00:00:09,760
Good thing I went to the hairdresser,
otherwise you wouldn't even look at me.

3
00:00:09,840 --> 00:00:12,520
They're giving you a compliment.
Instead of saying thanks, you're complaining.

4
00:00:12,600 --> 00:00:14,000
I'm not complaining. I'm just stating a fact,

5
00:00:14,080 --> 00:00:17,040
that it's really nice you noticed I went to the hairdresser.
-It really is nice.

6
00:00:17,120 --> 00:00:18,040
Thanks.

7
00:00:18,120 --> 00:00:20,800
What’s this? Did you dye it? Cut it?
-No, what are you talking about? Dye it, cut it?

8
00:00:20,880 --> 00:00:24,600
Just tidied it up a bit.
New hairdresser, wanted to switch it up, got bored.

9
00:00:24,680 --> 00:00:25,920
Rich people's problems.

10
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:28,440
Do you know how long it’s been since I went to a hairdresser?

11
00:00:28,520 --> 00:00:31,120
How long, a month? Two months?
-What, I wish. At least six months.

12
00:00:31,960 --> 00:00:34,560
We can't afford
for me to go to the hairdresser every month, you know.

13
00:00:34,640 --> 00:00:37,000
If I went to the hairdresser every month,
my hairdresser would have opened a bank account.

14
00:00:37,560 --> 00:00:39,400
Then going to the bank would be much nicer.

15
00:00:39,880 --> 00:00:41,680
Some wouldn’t even switch banks for that.

16
00:00:43,160 --> 00:00:45,280
So, how much did it cost, the hairdresser?
-Dad, are you mad?

17
00:00:46,120 --> 00:00:47,840
No, honey. He’s just jealous he doesn’t have hair.

18
00:00:48,160 --> 00:00:50,440
But he has hair in his nose.
-Shh. What...

19
00:00:56,880 --> 00:00:59,320
Oh, look.
-What is it?

20
00:01:00,120 --> 00:01:02,680
I found this little bag here.
-Open it. Let’s see what’s inside.

21
00:01:07,760 --> 00:01:11,160
Wow...
-Ben Porat Yosef, blessed be His name.

22
00:01:14,560 --> 00:01:16,880
Look at me, look at me and...

23
00:01:25,720 --> 00:01:27,560
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

24
00:01:27,880 --> 00:01:31,680
Hurry up. Girls, girls,
go draw on the porch. Here are your colors.

25
00:01:32,520 --> 00:01:33,920
Shabbat, Shani.
-What?

26
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:35,280
Not a word to my parents.

27
00:01:35,360 --> 00:01:37,840
Why? What, do you really think
those jewels are real?

28
00:01:37,920 --> 00:01:41,200
What, you think I know anything about this?
But I’m just raising a question, you know.

29
00:01:41,920 --> 00:01:44,160
If they’re not fake, would you share them?

30
00:01:44,240 --> 00:01:47,760
There’s nothing to raise and no sharing.
We’re returning this to the police.

31
00:01:48,320 --> 00:01:50,840
On Sunday.
-No. I’m calling now for them to send a squad car.

32
00:01:50,920 --> 00:01:54,640
But let’s think about it.
-I thought about it, I’m calling the police.

33
00:01:54,720 --> 00:01:56,560
Sit down, sweetie, why the police?

34
00:01:57,120 --> 00:02:01,080
Police means courts, restraining orders,
social workers...

35
00:02:01,160 --> 00:02:03,000
Those are stories no one comes out of well.

36
00:02:03,080 --> 00:02:06,520
Riki, Riki, what happened?
I volunteered for the civil guard once,

37
00:02:06,600 --> 00:02:09,600
if that helps.
-Maybe show them what we found downstairs, Shai.

38
00:02:10,320 --> 00:02:11,640
Thanks, Shabbat.

39
00:02:13,560 --> 00:02:16,400
We found this little bag

40
00:02:17,680 --> 00:02:19,200
and inside it...
-A treasure?

41
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:20,880
More or less.

42
00:02:23,080 --> 00:02:24,200
Oh...

43
00:02:24,280 --> 00:02:25,280
Zamir.

44
00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:26,320
Did you notify the police?

45
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:28,800
Why the police?
-See, you get it?

46
00:02:28,880 --> 00:02:33,000
Why the police? Tell me, don’t you have any sense?

47
00:02:33,200 --> 00:02:35,040
If we found it, it’s ours.

48
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:38,480
No, that’s not true.
It belongs to someone and they’re probably looking for it.

49
00:02:38,560 --> 00:02:41,440
I’m sure they’ll be happy! They’ll probably reward you somehow.

50
00:02:41,520 --> 00:02:43,720
What reward...
-What “you”...

51
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,120
Well, it doesn’t matter now and it’s not up for discussion.

52
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:49,440
Riki, think that maybe there’s a person who planned
to sell those family jewels

53
00:02:49,520 --> 00:02:51,960
for money for medicine. Do you understand?
How will I sleep at night?

54
00:02:52,040 --> 00:02:53,760
You’ll sleep just fine at night.

55
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:56,880
If it was important to him, he should have
taken better care of it.

56
00:02:56,960 --> 00:03:01,720
He should have considered that if someone
found it, they wouldn’t return it.

57
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:02,720
Riki...
Sit down...

58
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:04,120
Shai...
-Pinchas...

59
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:05,600
Sorry, it was at a fast pace.

60
00:03:06,160 --> 00:03:09,600
Sit down, sweetie, how do you not see that Shai is right?

61
00:03:10,320 --> 00:03:13,200
I don’t get it. God sends you a gift,

62
00:03:13,280 --> 00:03:15,120
and it just happens to arrive on Shabbat,

63
00:03:15,200 --> 00:03:19,160
and another thing, if God wanted
it to go to the police,

64
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:22,280
couldn’t He have just
left it by the police station?

65
00:03:22,360 --> 00:03:25,800
Riki, remind me,
isn’t God the one who said "don’t steal"?

66
00:03:26,360 --> 00:03:29,280
Wait. Who stole? Who was stolen from?

67
00:03:29,520 --> 00:03:33,640
And what’s with the commandments all of a sudden?
Why bring up God for everything?

68
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:36,160
You know you shouldn’t take His name in vain?

69
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:41,040
Oh, the schnitzels...
-the schnitzels!

70
00:03:43,480 --> 00:03:44,600
The schnitzels...

71
00:03:46,200 --> 00:03:47,040
What’s going on?

72
00:03:48,080 --> 00:03:49,280
What, everything’s fine with the schnitzels.

73
00:03:49,360 --> 00:03:51,840
I just wanted to call you.
-Mom, that’s not nice.

74
00:03:51,920 --> 00:03:54,520
You don’t do things like that.
-Don’t let her call the police.

75
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:56,840
Mom, she’s his wife.
-And...

76
00:03:57,200 --> 00:04:01,080
And... the girls saw we found it too.

77
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:04,120
So what kind of education is that?
-Education is good only in theory.

78
00:04:04,200 --> 00:04:06,880
In practice, everything’s corrupt in our country.

79
00:04:07,440 --> 00:04:10,200
From the head of the wolf, it’s rotten all the way down,

80
00:04:10,760 --> 00:04:13,240
the fish are spoiled and the stench reaches the heavens.

81
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:17,000
I’ll tell you what will happen. She’ll call
the police, they’ll come take it

82
00:04:17,079 --> 00:04:18,880
and then they’ll keep it for themselves.

83
00:04:18,959 --> 00:04:21,279
Uh-huh, and there’s no moral issue here?

84
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:24,720
Morality never stopped anyone from anything,

85
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:27,200
it just didn’t let anyone enjoy it.

86
00:04:29,560 --> 00:04:32,200
Fine. Pinchas, I’m calling the police.
-Wait, wait, sit down.

87
00:04:32,280 --> 00:04:36,000
If you call the police and it turns out
it’s just a little girl’s toy jewelry?

88
00:04:36,080 --> 00:04:37,560
Wait a second, we need to check.

89
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:41,040
I have a magnifying glass here.

90
00:04:41,880 --> 00:04:44,880
Yes. Let me check. One second.

91
00:04:59,560 --> 00:05:01,200
What, what, what? Do you know about this, Pinchas?

92
00:05:01,280 --> 00:05:03,720
Not really, but I saw someone do it once.

93
00:05:04,960 --> 00:05:08,160
Fine, I’m calling the police.
-Shabbat Shalom.

94
00:05:08,240 --> 00:05:09,600
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

95
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:13,680
What’s this? Did you guys rob a bank?

96
00:05:14,240 --> 00:05:17,680
Of course, Shai found it.
-What, is all this crap real?

97
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:21,280
Tell me, are you guys crazy?
You just throw this on the table?

98
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:23,600
The door’s open, anyone can walk in.
-Shabbat Shalom.

99
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:25,480
Honey, lock the door.
-Why lock it?

100
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:27,760
Shai found this bag with Itamar in the suburbs.

101
00:05:27,840 --> 00:05:29,840
Wow, some poor guy lost this.

102
00:05:29,920 --> 00:05:32,600
Honey, if someone lost something like this,
then he’s not poor.

103
00:05:32,680 --> 00:05:34,440
Itamar, it doesn’t matter. We need to return it.

104
00:05:34,520 --> 00:05:36,440
Right.
-What do you mean return it? Return what?

105
00:05:36,520 --> 00:05:39,120
Sorry, we need to share it among everyone
and peace on Israel.

106
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:43,120
Itamar, we’re returning it.
-Fine, Itamar, I really don’t think like you

107
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:45,320
and I’m going to call the police now.
-Tell me, are you normal?

108
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:47,960
Do you think the Israeli police
have time to deal with this bag?

109
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:50,880
There’s a derby going on now.
-There are actually some really nice things here.

110
00:05:50,960 --> 00:05:52,760
Michal, please return it.
-Sit down,

111
00:05:52,840 --> 00:05:54,040
sit down.
-What?

112
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:57,120
Where are you taking this?
-It doesn’t matter. The main thing is, far from others.

113
00:05:57,760 --> 00:05:59,080
But...
-Sit down, sit down.

114
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:01,200
I’m calling the police.

115
00:06:01,760 --> 00:06:02,680
Shabbat Shalom.

116
00:06:03,160 --> 00:06:05,240
Did you see the bag?
-Where did you find it?

117
00:06:05,320 --> 00:06:07,800
Down here, by the parking lot.
-Were there any other bags there?

118
00:06:09,240 --> 00:06:11,840
I didn’t look.
-How didn’t you look? Maybe there are more?

119
00:06:11,920 --> 00:06:14,840
I’m not... I’m running to check downstairs.
Don’t let her call the police.

120
00:06:14,920 --> 00:06:16,680
Come on...
-Honey, come with you?

121
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:18,640
Sit down...
-What?

122
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:22,600
You know I don't... I don't like
getting involved in other people's business.

123
00:06:22,680 --> 00:06:25,600
Riki, I'm really sorry
but I didn't come to talk about the jewelry,

124
00:06:25,680 --> 00:06:27,480
I came to call the police.
-No, no, no. It's fine.

125
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:30,560
It's not about that at all. You're totally right. Of course.

126
00:06:30,640 --> 00:06:34,600
The connection between the girls is the most important.
I'm not that much of a witch.

127
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:36,920
No, I... I didn't say you're a witch.

128
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:39,040
Oh, thank you. At least that's something.

129
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:48,920
Riki, I'm sorry. What... what did you want to say?

130
00:06:49,960 --> 00:06:52,560
Forget it, it's not...
-Okay, I'm sorry. What...

131
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:55,240
I'm listening. What?
-No, I'm just thinking

132
00:06:55,320 --> 00:06:58,120
that you might think it's nonsense, everything I wanted to tell you.

133
00:06:58,200 --> 00:07:00,280
No, no. No. Come on, what? Come here.

134
00:07:00,960 --> 00:07:02,000
I just passed by and saw

135
00:07:02,080 --> 00:07:07,480
they opened that new plastic surgery clinic here,

136
00:07:07,880 --> 00:07:10,000
so I thought with your situation,

137
00:07:10,440 --> 00:07:12,920
you're just in time to start looking into it.

138
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:17,240
What did you want to talk about?
-Forget it, it suddenly seems to me not...

139
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:19,680
No, wait a second, Riki - I wanted you to...

140
00:07:19,760 --> 00:07:23,320
Do you think I need plastic surgery or something?

141
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:25,320
What do you mean "think"?

142
00:07:25,400 --> 00:07:28,960
I think if you want to catch it in time,

143
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:31,560
you start at your age.
-At my age?

144
00:07:31,640 --> 00:07:35,080
When things in the body start to age
you need to refresh them.

145
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:38,160
That's great.
-So you think I...

146
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:39,720
should only think ahead.

147
00:07:41,280 --> 00:07:43,680
I'm afraid I understand too much.

148
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:46,800
Riki, I don't need any surgeries!

149
00:07:47,360 --> 00:07:48,800
Are you sure?
-Yes.

150
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:54,800
Come on
and let's see

151
00:07:55,440 --> 00:07:59,840
I have a good friend from the kibbutz,
and she has a really good friend,

152
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:03,160
a widow. She looks amazing!

153
00:08:03,240 --> 00:08:05,640
She doesn't look a day over thirty.

154
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:07,960
And she did all the treatments.

155
00:08:08,520 --> 00:08:10,680
And now she's living it up,
flirting with whoever she wants,

156
00:08:10,760 --> 00:08:12,800
mostly with younger guys.

157
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:15,880
But those treatments cost a fortune.

158
00:08:16,440 --> 00:08:18,640
What did she do, at a very young age?

159
00:08:18,720 --> 00:08:23,800
She started a savings plan, a little money for a rainy day.

160
00:08:23,880 --> 00:08:26,560
But why do I need to think a rainy day will come?

161
00:08:27,120 --> 00:08:31,040
When the eyelids droop, all you see is black.

162
00:08:36,760 --> 00:08:38,360
There's nothing.
-Did you look well?

163
00:08:38,679 --> 00:08:40,720
Of course, babe. Tell me, tell me,

164
00:08:41,360 --> 00:08:44,120
who are you planning to sell this to?
-I don't know. What...

165
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:46,240
Maybe you should post "Jewelry for Sale" online?

166
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:48,440
Yeah. Sure, babe. And then everyone who lost it will come

167
00:08:48,520 --> 00:08:50,800
and also those who really lost it,
and all the jewelry will be gone.

168
00:08:50,880 --> 00:08:52,760
Yeah, but I'm also afraid the police will find out we're selling

169
00:08:52,840 --> 00:08:54,720
and then they'll catch us
and think we stole it.

170
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:56,680
What are you worried about, Shai?
She'll come to bail you out.

171
00:08:56,760 --> 00:08:58,720
With the money from the jewelry
she can bail you out

172
00:08:58,800 --> 00:09:01,680
and on the way, get Shai's cops
into early retirement.

173
00:09:01,760 --> 00:09:05,320
I can't believe you guys are sitting
in my living room talking like thieves.

174
00:09:05,400 --> 00:09:08,960
Who are we going to sell to, the police will catch us,
bail outs from detention...

175
00:09:09,040 --> 00:09:12,160
In the end, only you will get arrested, Pini, because you're the homeowner.

176
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:15,440
Enough, babe, don't stress him out.
-What, but I don't understand you.

177
00:09:15,520 --> 00:09:18,240
Shai said she's calling the police. Right?
-No, she's with Mom, so no way.

178
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:21,360
Shai, come here for a second.
-I'm coming.

179
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:22,360
Stay strong.

180
00:09:26,560 --> 00:09:27,600
Babe, what's going on?

181
00:09:29,160 --> 00:09:32,120
Your mom talked to me.
-I know. She talked to me too.

182
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:34,440
I really want to understand
how she dares to say something like that to me.

183
00:09:35,480 --> 00:09:38,200
Babe, that's my mom,

184
00:09:38,920 --> 00:09:42,120
she's been through a thing or two. She's confident about it.

185
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:44,680
And that somehow gives her
the right to interfere in my life?

186
00:09:47,240 --> 00:09:49,960
Maybe you just... didn't understand her properly.

187
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:52,960
She just wants what's best for you! For me.

188
00:09:53,040 --> 00:09:56,440
Oh, what's best for me? How does that relate to your benefit?

189
00:09:57,000 --> 00:10:00,240
Because in the end, I should enjoy it too.

190
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:04,240
Right?
-Yeah, kind of.

191
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:06,800
True. Okay, so here,

192
00:10:07,280 --> 00:10:09,280
Come on, tell me what I should do?

193
00:10:10,040 --> 00:10:12,920
Okay, I think the best thing to do

194
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:16,320
is just to go with the flow.
-Oh. Go with the flow?

195
00:10:16,400 --> 00:10:17,560
Yeah.
-Go with the flow.

196
00:10:17,880 --> 00:10:19,840
What do you mean "go with the flow"?
What do you want me to go with?

197
00:10:20,160 --> 00:10:22,240
What do you want me to do?
Should I bring it up? Should I stretch it?

198
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:23,880
Should I enlarge? What's wrong with that?
-What to enlarge?

199
00:10:23,960 --> 00:10:25,800
Wait, babe, babe, what are we talking about?

200
00:10:25,880 --> 00:10:28,520
About what? About all this stuff,
about eyelid lifts, breast enlargements,

201
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:30,800
facelifts...
-What? You don't need any of that.

202
00:10:30,880 --> 00:10:33,160
Who put those nonsense ideas in your head?
-Your mom.

203
00:10:33,240 --> 00:10:34,800
So my mom doesn't know what she's talking about.

204
00:10:34,880 --> 00:10:37,760
Yeah, but she's been through some things in life.
After all, she's your mom.

205
00:10:37,840 --> 00:10:41,160
Babe, eyelid lifts? What’s that? You're perfect.

206
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:44,600
Okay. Now I'm perfect?
You're just annoying! You're not objective either.

207
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:47,720
Yeah? You know what?
You want me to take a nude photo of you

208
00:10:47,800 --> 00:10:49,520
and send it to some friends?
-Oh, do me a favor.

209
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:51,800
Objective.
-Do me a favor, Shai. Really. D.

210
00:10:52,640 --> 00:10:54,840
Where's Shai?
-With Shai in the bedroom.

211
00:10:55,400 --> 00:10:58,880
Well, I think it'll be fine.
-What's fine?

212
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:00,920
Say, where's Adam? What's going on with him?

213
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:03,920
He called saying he's running a bit late,
he's coming with someone new.

214
00:11:04,480 --> 00:11:07,760
Listen, I don't think we should talk to Adam

215
00:11:07,840 --> 00:11:09,640
about the whole jewelry thing.

216
00:11:09,720 --> 00:11:11,560
You never know what kind of jewelry he'll bring.

217
00:11:11,640 --> 00:11:14,160
And every time he surprises us more.
-What are you talking about?

218
00:11:14,720 --> 00:11:17,280
About Adam, he's coming with someone new.

219
00:11:17,840 --> 00:11:19,080
Well, I'm going to the kitchen.

220
00:11:19,160 --> 00:11:21,080
Michal, I need you for a second in the room.

221
00:11:22,200 --> 00:11:23,800
Shabbat Shalom.

222
00:11:23,880 --> 00:11:25,320
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

223
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:27,880
Hello.
-Hey. Itamar.

224
00:11:27,960 --> 00:11:30,160
Nice to meet you.
-Nice to meet you. Mili. Hello.

225
00:11:30,240 --> 00:11:31,080
Shai.

226
00:11:31,560 --> 00:11:32,640
Hi.
-Do we know each other?

227
00:11:33,720 --> 00:11:34,600
I don't think so.
-No?

228
00:11:34,680 --> 00:11:36,120
No.
-Adam.

229
00:11:36,720 --> 00:11:38,640
Yeah. This is Pinchas, my dad.

230
00:11:38,720 --> 00:11:39,840
Nice to meet you.
-Nice to meet you, Shabbat Shalom.

231
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:41,240
Nice to meet you, Mili.

232
00:11:41,320 --> 00:11:43,160
Sit down. Michal.
-Let's go to the room.

233
00:11:44,600 --> 00:11:48,720
So, Mili? Mili. What do you do?

234
00:11:48,800 --> 00:11:49,680
Adam!

235
00:11:49,760 --> 00:11:53,360
I can hear your voice,
aren't you coming to say hello to your mom

236
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:56,120
and introduce me to your new girlfriend...

237
00:11:58,600 --> 00:12:02,120
Mili Tavalet?

238
00:12:03,240 --> 00:12:04,120
Wow, Roko.

239
00:12:07,440 --> 00:12:08,640
Did you see her? She's stunning.

240
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:10,880
Next week she won't be here anymore. Listen for a second.
-What?

241
00:12:10,960 --> 00:12:13,800
I want to ask you something
and I really want you to be honest with me.

242
00:12:13,880 --> 00:12:15,760
Just tell me the truth, even if it's
a bit uncomfortable for you. Okay?

243
00:12:16,320 --> 00:12:17,720
Sure. What... what's the deal?

244
00:12:18,880 --> 00:12:21,400
Look at me for a second, Michal, and tell me, really tell me.

245
00:12:22,840 --> 00:12:27,120
Do you think I need
some kind of cosmetic touch-up?

246
00:12:27,680 --> 00:12:29,160
Definitely.
-What?

247
00:12:29,240 --> 00:12:32,600
Like, just a little bit,
you know, nothing dramatic,

248
00:12:32,680 --> 00:12:35,960
but yeah, you need like... you know,
for maintenance. Like, a specific treatment.

249
00:12:36,160 --> 00:12:37,840
Specific treatment?
-Specific, Riki.

250
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:43,440
That's Mili Tabavlat.
-Do I know her?

251
00:12:43,520 --> 00:12:46,040
Gershon's widow.
-Which Gershon?

252
00:12:46,600 --> 00:12:48,600
Tabavlat.
-The one who passed away?

253
00:12:48,680 --> 00:12:50,720
Yeah.
-I didn't know his daughter.

254
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:51,960
How would I know who she is?

255
00:12:52,040 --> 00:12:54,240
How's his daughter? That's his widow.

256
00:12:54,880 --> 00:12:57,640
She was that young?
-Well, no.

257
00:12:58,360 --> 00:13:01,240
Did you see what they did to her?
-No way!

258
00:13:04,800 --> 00:13:06,480
You didn't tell me you're Riki Rosen's son.

259
00:13:07,400 --> 00:13:12,240
Wait, so what's your connection to Mom?
-We have a mutual friend, Fanny.

260
00:13:13,120 --> 00:13:14,480
Fanny from the country club?

261
00:13:14,560 --> 00:13:17,560
What, you all know her?
-Only from stories.

262
00:13:17,640 --> 00:13:20,240
What a coincidence. Why didn't you tell me
you're friends with Fanny from the country club?

263
00:13:20,320 --> 00:13:22,960
You didn't ask, dear.
-Listen, it's really refreshing.

264
00:13:23,040 --> 00:13:24,920
After all the girls Adam hangs out with,

265
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:26,880
it's nice to see someone who's more...

266
00:13:26,960 --> 00:13:29,640
Are you serious?
-No, no, no. It's fine, it's fine.

267
00:13:29,720 --> 00:13:30,960
It's fine.
-I'm just pointing out the fact

268
00:13:31,040 --> 00:13:33,520
that you look over 35 and that's...

269
00:13:33,600 --> 00:13:36,720
And when guys date younger girls,
what's up with that, is that okay?

270
00:13:37,520 --> 00:13:39,720
That's not accurate, because when young girls date older guys,

271
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:41,200
they say it's because of their money.

272
00:13:41,760 --> 00:13:44,720
Sorry, it depends on the age gap.
-What age gap?

273
00:13:45,440 --> 00:13:46,280
Honey, come here for a sec.

274
00:13:46,360 --> 00:13:48,080
I have to, sweetie?
-Yeah, sweetie.

275
00:13:48,960 --> 00:13:50,920
Okay, sweetie.
-Get up, sweetie!

276
00:13:54,920 --> 00:13:57,440
Umm... okay, so first of all

277
00:13:57,520 --> 00:13:59,120
I want to say you look amazing.

278
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:02,120
I need your surgeon's phone number.

279
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:04,080
You probably remember it by heart. How does it go?

280
00:14:05,720 --> 00:14:09,200
I won't let my little boy
date Mili Tabavlat.

281
00:14:09,280 --> 00:14:12,080
She could be his mom.
-Yeah, but what can you do?

282
00:14:12,160 --> 00:14:16,200
We need to separate them
before the glue dries.

283
00:14:16,280 --> 00:14:19,320
I know this Mili, she's super clingy.

284
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:21,440
Okay, I'm going to tell him
you won't let this happen.

285
00:14:21,520 --> 00:14:23,800
No. If you do that, he'll do the opposite

286
00:14:23,880 --> 00:14:26,280
and you'll get the opposite result.
-So what do we do?

287
00:14:26,960 --> 00:14:29,880
We need to do "divide and conquer."
I'll take Mili to the kitchen,

288
00:14:29,960 --> 00:14:31,520
you stay with Adam.

289
00:14:32,080 --> 00:14:34,640
I just talked to Michal
and she said I need to.

290
00:14:34,720 --> 00:14:37,440
Need what?
-Those cosmetic treatments,

291
00:14:37,520 --> 00:14:39,960
she knows about these things.
Did I tell you you're not objective?

292
00:14:40,040 --> 00:14:42,720
Honey, you really don't need anything!

293
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:45,240
So why did she say that?
-Because she's messed up in the head.

294
00:14:45,320 --> 00:14:49,000
Your mom said the same.
-Because my mom's messed up in the head too.

295
00:14:50,040 --> 00:14:51,040
That's true.

296
00:14:53,320 --> 00:14:56,280
Just so you know, more and more guys
are getting surgeries lately.

297
00:14:56,360 --> 00:14:58,320
Honestly, I don't need
any of that.

298
00:14:58,400 --> 00:15:00,960
I'm perfect.
-Maybe a hair transplant?

299
00:15:01,320 --> 00:15:03,200
Sorry, that's an optical choice.

300
00:15:03,280 --> 00:15:04,120
Mili.

301
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:05,600
Yeah.
-Can you come to the kitchen with me for a sec?

302
00:15:06,240 --> 00:15:08,640
Sure, I'd love to help.

303
00:15:09,600 --> 00:15:12,720
Crazy, right?
What, do they know each other?

304
00:15:12,800 --> 00:15:14,800
Tell me, how old is she?
-Older.

305
00:15:14,880 --> 00:15:17,120
Forty?
-I don't know.

306
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:20,160
My man, she's over fifty.

307
00:15:20,240 --> 00:15:22,480
What fifty?
-What, haven't you seen her?

308
00:15:22,560 --> 00:15:25,120
Fifty and... not a little bit.

309
00:15:25,680 --> 00:15:27,720
Admica, tell me,

310
00:15:29,440 --> 00:15:33,040
Why do you need to date someone
who's older than you by a few terms?

311
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:34,800
How many terms are we talking about?

312
00:15:35,440 --> 00:15:37,760
Turns out it's twenty years or more.
-How do you know?

313
00:15:38,360 --> 00:15:42,080
Admica, I don't think
you should date a widow.

314
00:15:42,160 --> 00:15:44,200
You even knew the late husband.
-Ugh...

315
00:15:44,840 --> 00:15:47,440
Look, listen! I'm good.
I have no idea how old she is,

316
00:15:47,520 --> 00:15:50,160
I don't know who her husband was,
I don't know where she works,

317
00:15:50,240 --> 00:15:53,200
And I don't care. She's got a body... amazing.

318
00:15:53,440 --> 00:15:55,200
What's wrong with you?
-Adam...

319
00:15:55,280 --> 00:15:59,280
We want you to bring home a woman
to have kids and a family with,

320
00:15:59,360 --> 00:16:00,880
like it should be.

321
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:03,720
Why? So I can rush into all the poop and diapers?

322
00:16:03,800 --> 00:16:08,440
No, because with Mili's age, you'll be dealing
with diapers from the other end, Admica.

323
00:16:11,480 --> 00:16:14,360
So, how's it going, Mili?
-I'm doing great.

324
00:16:14,440 --> 00:16:17,200
Lately, I can say I'm really thriving.

325
00:16:17,280 --> 00:16:19,840
I can see that. And how's work?

326
00:16:20,400 --> 00:16:23,840
Work's been really busy lately
but I'm not complaining.

327
00:16:24,640 --> 00:16:28,000
Tell me, queen, what are you doing with him?

328
00:16:29,240 --> 00:16:30,480
Do you want me to go into detail?

329
00:16:33,280 --> 00:16:34,760
Do you think I need to save her from Mom?

330
00:16:34,840 --> 00:16:37,240
They're friends of Fanny from the cafeteria. What’s there to save?

331
00:16:37,520 --> 00:16:39,280
If you need help, just say so.

332
00:16:39,640 --> 00:16:42,400
Especially now that Shai found some treasure

333
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:44,520
Treasure... a little bag.

334
00:16:44,600 --> 00:16:47,920
So if you need help, just say.
Tell me, are you in a relationship?

335
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:51,800
Do me a favor...
-What, are you a ladyboy?

336
00:16:55,120 --> 00:16:57,280
Hello, Adam. Cutie.

337
00:16:58,280 --> 00:16:59,720
Yeah.
-Why are you so angry?

338
00:17:00,600 --> 00:17:02,640
Mili and my mom...
-What, they don't get along?

339
00:17:02,720 --> 00:17:04,599
More than that, they're friends from the cafeteria.

340
00:17:04,680 --> 00:17:09,079
Mom! What’s this, how old is she?
-Older than I thought.

341
00:17:10,280 --> 00:17:11,720
You're not doing this to your mom on purpose, are you?

342
00:17:12,280 --> 00:17:13,160
Not this time.

343
00:17:15,640 --> 00:17:18,560
Listen, if this is the girl you're willing
to fight with your family over,

344
00:17:19,440 --> 00:17:21,160
then go for it.
-Okay, okay.

345
00:17:26,079 --> 00:17:28,280
Look what plastic surgery can do.

346
00:17:34,600 --> 00:17:37,920
I want you to understand him. He needs
to find the woman of his life.

347
00:17:38,720 --> 00:17:41,320
You just want him as a pet.

348
00:17:41,400 --> 00:17:44,480
So go find yourself a cat, a dog,

349
00:17:44,560 --> 00:17:46,480
sushi, but understand him.

350
00:17:46,560 --> 00:17:48,840
It's not like he was innocent.

351
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:53,400
I'm against it, Mili.
I demand you leave him alone.

352
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:55,080
Of course.

353
00:17:56,640 --> 00:17:59,960
So everyone’s messed up in their heads?
-Who else did you ask?

354
00:18:00,040 --> 00:18:03,160
Doesn't matter. Adam.

355
00:18:03,720 --> 00:18:06,320
Adam. And his opinion matters to you?

356
00:18:06,400 --> 00:18:09,000
Why not?
-Did you see what kind of girls he hangs out with?

357
00:18:09,720 --> 00:18:10,640
I prefer a woman.

358
00:18:11,640 --> 00:18:13,680
Is that your way of telling me I'm ugly?

359
00:18:14,440 --> 00:18:18,320
Babe, you're not a model but you're perfect.

360
00:18:18,400 --> 00:18:21,080
You fit me just right in all the right places.

361
00:18:21,800 --> 00:18:24,360
You're growing up, nice.

362
00:18:25,080 --> 00:18:28,440
I'm just saying, I like to look at you like this.

363
00:18:30,520 --> 00:18:31,720
Well, you're not exactly a saint either.

364
00:18:33,480 --> 00:18:36,400
Fine. But I could... let’s say I could promote...

365
00:18:38,040 --> 00:18:38,960
Welding masks.

366
00:18:41,040 --> 00:18:42,640
There's no middle ground, you know.
-True.

367
00:18:45,960 --> 00:18:47,800
Dad, give him a few days, he’ll ditch you on his own.

368
00:18:47,880 --> 00:18:50,680
What "a few days"?
You know what Mom can do to me in a few days?

369
00:18:51,240 --> 00:18:52,400
It's a soul possession.

370
00:18:53,560 --> 00:18:54,920
Adam.
-What?

371
00:18:55,840 --> 00:18:58,200
I forbid you to date Mili Tavalet.

372
00:18:58,280 --> 00:18:59,920
Dad, what are you doing?

373
00:19:00,480 --> 00:19:02,840
Riki, just let me, I’ll handle it gently.

374
00:19:02,920 --> 00:19:05,520
Gently. I’m crazy about him.
-Me too.

375
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:08,400
Gently!
-Gently, gently.

376
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:11,040
And this
“And this

377
00:19:11,120 --> 00:19:15,600
Oh, here, meet her. Sit down, this is Mili Tavalet.

378
00:19:15,680 --> 00:19:18,720
I was just telling her about you today.
-Shai, nice to meet you.

379
00:19:18,800 --> 00:19:22,280
What a coincidence, wow, because when you said "Mili Tavalet"

380
00:19:22,360 --> 00:19:23,960
I didn’t... I didn’t picture you like this.

381
00:19:24,520 --> 00:19:26,160
Mili, tell me,

382
00:19:27,240 --> 00:19:30,080
what things would you suggest she renovate

383
00:19:30,160 --> 00:19:32,720
if she had enough money to renovate?

384
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:36,120
Mom, please, leave Shabi alone,
she doesn’t need any insurance.

385
00:19:36,200 --> 00:19:39,560
Since when do you understand this? It’s just between women,

386
00:19:39,640 --> 00:19:42,960
it’s not a guy thing at all,
and if you’re going to the living room,

387
00:19:43,040 --> 00:19:45,840
invite everyone. We’re about to start eating.

388
00:19:46,720 --> 00:19:47,800
Stay strong.

389
00:19:48,760 --> 00:19:50,640
Shai, nice...
-Nice to meet you.

390
00:19:54,800 --> 00:19:57,120
Let’s eat before Mom
drives Shabi even crazier.

391
00:19:57,480 --> 00:20:01,960
Adam, my sweet, there’s such a big age gap
it’s impossible to bridge.

392
00:20:02,040 --> 00:20:04,000
Why? Look, it works for me and Itamar.

393
00:20:04,080 --> 00:20:07,280
Right, babe?
-Yeah, but babe, it’s not the same case.

394
00:20:07,360 --> 00:20:08,880
Are you coming? Girls!

395
00:20:11,800 --> 00:20:13,880
Why did you have to bring this up now? Huh?

396
00:20:14,480 --> 00:20:15,440
Little fool.

397
00:20:15,920 --> 00:20:17,080
So tell me, babe,

398
00:20:17,160 --> 00:20:19,360
how much money are you willing
to spend on stuff like this?

399
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:23,360
Well, Shabi, no one here but me
thinks you need to do anything.

400
00:20:23,440 --> 00:20:26,200
And your mom.
-My mom doesn’t say anything

401
00:20:26,280 --> 00:20:29,400
unless she has some hidden agenda.
-What do you mean? What agenda?

402
00:20:29,480 --> 00:20:33,360
She’s probably all about those surgeries
because she wants something else.

403
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:35,880
Try to think about what.
-What? No...

404
00:20:35,960 --> 00:20:37,760
What interest does she have?
-When did she tell you that?

405
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:41,360
Look at what it says.
-How nice. What is it?

406
00:20:41,840 --> 00:20:44,520
It’s an ad, saying whoever lost the pouch, it’s with us.

407
00:20:44,600 --> 00:20:46,320
Nice.
Pretty.

408
00:20:47,640 --> 00:20:50,120
The pouch... like it’s a doll
for the jewelry inside?

409
00:20:50,680 --> 00:20:53,400
What jewelry? Pouch...
-No, no.

410
00:20:53,480 --> 00:20:55,000
No, no, no, no.
-No, no.

411
00:20:55,080 --> 00:20:56,920
What are we talking about?
-Where’s my phone?

412
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:58,160
Shai, what did you even say to her?

413
00:20:58,240 --> 00:21:01,760
Turns out Shai found a pouch with jewelry earlier.
-Wow...

414
00:21:01,840 --> 00:21:04,360
Where are you calling?
-The police. She wants to return them.

415
00:21:04,440 --> 00:21:06,200
Adam.
-Come on, are you guys out of your minds?

416
00:21:06,280 --> 00:21:07,960
What, don’t you remember what Mom always says?

417
00:21:08,040 --> 00:21:10,000
That in the police, the fish stinks...
-No, no...

418
00:21:10,080 --> 00:21:12,320
...from head to tail or something like that.
-No. No.

419
00:21:12,400 --> 00:21:13,680
They’ll keep it for themselves.
-No, no.

420
00:21:14,360 --> 00:21:15,400
What happened?

421
00:21:16,360 --> 00:21:20,160
What Riki's trying to say
is that I'm a deputy superintendent in the police,

422
00:21:20,400 --> 00:21:21,560
head of the investigations department.

423
00:21:22,280 --> 00:21:25,520
Just like Riki says.

424
00:21:25,600 --> 00:21:28,400
I don't think this will work out.
-I'm Shai, we're coming...

425
00:21:29,280 --> 00:21:31,760
Where are the jewelry, the bag, what did you find?
-Here, here.

426
00:21:31,840 --> 00:21:33,400
Take this, everything. We didn't take anything.

427
00:21:33,480 --> 00:21:35,880
I'll take this with me.
-Thanks.

428
00:21:36,760 --> 00:21:39,760
Still.
-Still, still.

429
00:21:42,320 --> 00:21:45,360
Mom was really frustrated.
-I keep thinking

430
00:21:45,440 --> 00:21:47,920
that I’ll postpone the surgery for a few weeks,

431
00:21:48,440 --> 00:21:50,520
but if you want to treat me,
I’d love a pampering day.

432
00:21:51,080 --> 00:21:55,280
If it’s cheaper than eyelid surgery...
-Of course. It’s the price of a third of an eyelid.

433
00:21:55,360 --> 00:21:57,080
Then I’ll treat you.
-Great.

434
00:21:57,440 --> 00:21:59,480
Are you treating me too?
-What do you want?

435
00:21:59,560 --> 00:22:03,160
I want a nice facial treatment.
-No. I’m really sorry, it’s very expensive,

436
00:22:03,240 --> 00:22:05,880
but I’m willing to invest in you a kilo of avocados from the market.

437
00:22:05,960 --> 00:22:07,640
I’ll mash it up, spread it all over your face,

438
00:22:07,720 --> 00:22:09,520
like this, you’ll be all green, it’s good for the skin.

439
00:22:09,600 --> 00:22:11,600
What green, what am I, Shrek?
-Which Shrek?

440
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:14,800
Does Shrek suit you? Maybe the donkey fits better.

441
00:22:18,520 --> 00:22:19,920
Riki, think that maybe there’s a person

442
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:25,040
who really planned, he planned
to sell this jewelry

443
00:22:25,120 --> 00:22:26,800
to maybe buy medicine...
-No, no.

444
00:22:29,360 --> 00:22:31,520
The wife... the widow of Gershon.

445
00:22:32,840 --> 00:22:34,880
I’ll run downstairs,
check if there’s another bag there.

446
00:22:34,960 --> 00:22:37,480
What happened to you? One bag is a sign of dozens of bags.

447
00:22:37,800 --> 00:22:40,200
Move, move, and Shai, don’t...
-This is too much.

448
00:22:41,560 --> 00:22:44,200
I have...
-Full as a pomegranate.

449
00:22:44,680 --> 00:22:46,640
But what do I care?
-Admica...

450
00:22:46,720 --> 00:22:49,080
She has a body... amazing. What’s wrong with you?

451
00:22:50,600 --> 00:22:53,080
Adam.
-Look at him.

452
00:22:53,160 --> 00:22:57,640
Got it? I’m bored.
-Oh, you’re bored. Rich people problems.

453
00:22:58,440 --> 00:23:01,200
But I want you to bring someone home...

454
00:23:02,960 --> 00:23:05,480
to have kids with you,

455
00:23:05,880 --> 00:23:07,160
a family...

